FOODBORNE DISEASE SURVEILLANCE - SPAIN (3)
==========================================
[In reply to the query for sources of information on
foodborne disease outbreaks in Spain:]

Data from our National Net of Epidemiological Surveillance are
systematically published in the BOLETIN EPIDEMIOLOGICO SEMANAL.
This includes information about food borne outbreaks and other
communicable diseases. Our Bulletin is free, distributed by
the National Center for Epidemiology.
Address for subscriptions:
Centro Nacional de Epidemiologia
Sinesio Delgado, 6
28029-MADRID, Spain
A version of this weekly bulletin is being prepared for WWW.
If you send us your [postal] mail address, we will be pleased to
send you current information on food borne diseases
published in the bulletin.
Thank you very much for your interest.
--
Ana Ruiz Bremon
e-mail: aruiz@isciii.es
